1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:10,000
[English subtitles are available]

2
00:01:24,850 --> 00:01:28,789
[The Fearless Season 1]

3
00:01:29,360 --> 00:01:31,700
[Episode 10]

4
00:01:38,310 --> 00:01:39,550
Open the door!

5
00:01:39,580 --> 00:01:41,000
Luo Yingzi, it's time to pay your debts!

6
00:01:41,000 --> 00:01:41,710
Hurry up!

7
00:01:43,320 --> 00:01:45,479
Open the door!

8
00:01:45,509 --> 00:01:48,190
Pay us!

9
00:01:52,580 --> 00:01:54,840
We represent the Civil Commercial Bank.

10
00:01:55,200 --> 00:01:56,750
Your husband Liu Ming owes us a loan

11
00:01:56,750 --> 00:01:58,310
that he should've repaid 3 months ago.

12
00:01:58,310 --> 00:01:59,750
Liu Ming wants children now.

13
00:01:59,750 --> 00:02:01,990
Open the door!

14
00:02:01,990 --> 00:02:03,150
Pay us! Pay us!

15
00:02:03,580 --> 00:02:04,110
Open the door!

16
00:02:04,110 --> 00:02:05,590
What's wrong with you?

17
00:02:05,590 --> 00:02:07,040
How could you not repay your loans?

18
00:02:07,040 --> 00:02:07,970
What's going on?

19
00:02:09,530 --> 00:02:10,240
Sorry.

20
00:02:10,270 --> 00:02:11,440
Sorry, Ms. Mei.

21
00:02:12,110 --> 00:02:13,440
Do you always stay alert

22
00:02:14,060 --> 00:02:15,650
when you're asleep?

23
00:02:22,150 --> 00:02:23,500
Since my husband

24
00:02:25,190 --> 00:02:26,270
ran away,

25
00:02:29,310 --> 00:02:31,910
I feel that bad things would happen.

26
00:02:35,440 --> 00:02:36,370
What is it about?

27
00:02:39,690 --> 00:02:40,329
He

28
00:02:41,900 --> 00:02:44,290
mortgaged our apartment.

29
00:02:45,570 --> 00:02:46,870
Then I was evicted from it

30
00:02:46,870 --> 00:02:48,329
by the bank.

31
00:02:52,550 --> 00:02:54,480
The court hasn't ruled yet, has it?

32
00:02:55,550 --> 00:02:58,370
Chen Shuo from Dazheng Law Firm

33
00:02:59,040 --> 00:03:00,080
played dirty.

34
00:03:01,280 --> 00:03:03,080
And the bank decided to go rogue.

35
00:03:05,020 --> 00:03:06,540
Move out, then.

36
00:03:07,300 --> 00:03:08,020
Thank you.

37
00:03:12,870 --> 00:03:13,600
Ms. Mei,

38
00:03:15,470 --> 00:03:17,579
It's just a very short time, isn't it?

39
00:03:22,730 --> 00:03:24,090
Before this happened,

40
00:03:25,590 --> 00:03:27,920
my life was comfortable without worries.

41
00:03:28,860 --> 00:03:30,270
I got too bored,

42
00:03:30,290 --> 00:03:31,940
so I took the bar exam.

43
00:03:35,150 --> 00:03:36,280
In a blink of an eye,

44
00:03:38,390 --> 00:03:39,820
my husband ran away,

45
00:03:41,170 --> 00:03:42,900
and left me with a load of debts.

46
00:03:43,710 --> 00:03:45,160
I have nowhere to go.

47
00:03:46,070 --> 00:03:48,590
I don't own a place anymore.

48
00:03:52,220 --> 00:03:53,480
The worst thing is that

49
00:03:53,890 --> 00:03:55,370
I don't know

50
00:03:55,400 --> 00:03:57,329
how I got myself in this situation.

51
00:04:00,750 --> 00:04:01,990
What have I done wrong

52
00:04:02,010 --> 00:04:03,740
to deserve all this suffering?

53
00:04:05,000 --> 00:04:06,370
I know how you feel.

54
00:04:10,830 --> 00:04:12,750
I was as hurt as you are 3 years ago.

55
00:04:28,670 --> 00:04:29,630
At that time,

56
00:04:30,660 --> 00:04:32,120
my husband Yu Daliang and I

57
00:04:32,440 --> 00:04:35,870
founded Liangcheng Law Firm.

58
00:04:36,930 --> 00:04:39,490
We ambitiously tried to build it

59
00:04:40,200 --> 00:04:43,430
into a top-class firm in the country.

60
00:04:45,250 --> 00:04:46,640
But suddenly,

61
00:04:48,430 --> 00:04:50,470
we were convicted of crimes.

62
00:04:52,700 --> 00:04:53,930
My husband

63
00:04:57,440 --> 00:04:58,880
collapsed in court.

64
00:05:00,880 --> 00:05:02,980
I was disbarred.

65
00:05:10,400 --> 00:05:11,400
Just like you,

66
00:05:13,110 --> 00:05:14,590
I didn't know

67
00:05:15,430 --> 00:05:16,890
how everything happened.

68
00:05:19,040 --> 00:05:20,280
Someone set us up.

69
00:05:21,820 --> 00:05:22,620
But who was it?

70
00:05:23,270 --> 00:05:24,800
Why would this person do so?

71
00:05:26,500 --> 00:05:28,120
I still can't figure it out.

72
00:05:30,470 --> 00:05:33,380
All of a sudden, I lost my husband, my home,

73
00:05:35,310 --> 00:05:37,560
my reputation and property.

74
00:05:39,120 --> 00:05:40,370
I changed my name

75
00:05:42,510 --> 00:05:44,390
into my husband's.

76
00:05:45,400 --> 00:05:46,590
You can imagine

77
00:05:47,570 --> 00:05:48,950
how I felt at that time.

78
00:05:51,290 --> 00:05:52,050
I insist

79
00:05:55,090 --> 00:05:57,110
that our names must be cleared.

80
00:06:04,970 --> 00:06:06,060
But until now,

81
00:06:09,590 --> 00:06:11,190
I haven't done anything yet.

82
00:06:14,790 --> 00:06:15,520
Ms. Mei,

83
00:06:18,030 --> 00:06:19,240
compared to you,

84
00:06:21,640 --> 00:06:24,210
what I've been through is trivial.

85
00:06:35,130 --> 00:06:36,280
Being alive

86
00:06:37,510 --> 00:06:38,640
is all that matters.

87
00:06:40,570 --> 00:06:41,670
We can only

88
00:06:43,330 --> 00:06:44,560
save ourselves.

89
00:07:05,620 --> 00:07:06,570
Why are you here?

90
00:07:06,970 --> 00:07:08,140
I came to see you.

91
00:07:08,500 --> 00:07:10,360
I wanted to know how you're doing.

92
00:07:10,620 --> 00:07:11,730
I'm doing great.

93
00:07:12,270 --> 00:07:14,200
I eat well and sleep well.

94
00:07:14,370 --> 00:07:16,180
Thank you for paying me a visit.

95
00:07:16,480 --> 00:07:17,740
I'm worried about you.

96
00:07:18,530 --> 00:07:20,080
Ms. Fang said you could take a few days off

97
00:07:20,080 --> 00:07:20,980
before going back to work.

98
00:07:20,980 --> 00:07:21,580
No need to.

99
00:07:21,760 --> 00:07:23,160
I’ll go to work tomorrow.

100
00:07:26,410 --> 00:07:28,810
Won't you consider Ms. Fang's suggestion?

101
00:07:29,290 --> 00:07:30,260
What suggestion?

102
00:07:30,260 --> 00:07:31,190
Call the police.

103
00:07:32,580 --> 00:07:34,400
If there is a criminal investigation,

104
00:07:34,400 --> 00:07:36,630
we can postpone the case about the bank.

105
00:07:36,950 --> 00:07:38,630
If Liu Ming is found guilty

106
00:07:38,659 --> 00:07:39,900
of maliciously creating debts,

107
00:07:39,900 --> 00:07:42,360
you'll have more advantages in the divorce.

108
00:07:44,990 --> 00:07:45,990
I...

109
00:07:47,570 --> 00:07:49,080
will think about it.

110
00:07:52,040 --> 00:07:52,900
You want a beer?

111
00:07:53,590 --> 00:07:54,430
I'd love one.

112
00:08:03,620 --> 00:08:05,420
Soon we'll put an end to all this.

113
00:08:06,370 --> 00:08:08,200
Yes. We will.

114
00:08:11,030 --> 00:08:12,430
Is it a human or an animal?

115
00:08:13,240 --> 00:08:13,960
An animal.

116
00:08:14,310 --> 00:08:15,150
Big or small?

117
00:08:15,460 --> 00:08:16,270
It can be both.

118
00:08:16,790 --> 00:08:18,320
What kind of answer is that?

119
00:08:18,660 --> 00:08:19,500
That's right.

120
00:08:19,520 --> 00:08:20,540
It can be big and small.

121
00:08:20,540 --> 00:08:21,270
It's true.

122
00:08:21,590 --> 00:08:23,760
"Meow" or "ruff"?

123
00:08:24,150 --> 00:08:25,070
You're cheating!

124
00:08:25,070 --> 00:08:25,730
I have no choice.

125
00:08:25,730 --> 00:08:26,400
It's "meow".

126
00:08:26,400 --> 00:08:27,830
I have to answer it, don't I?

127
00:08:27,830 --> 00:08:28,350
I've lost.

128
00:08:28,350 --> 00:08:29,840
You've all lost. Chug it!

129
00:08:38,110 --> 00:08:38,860
Thank you.

130
00:08:54,330 --> 00:08:55,330
Xinjiang people.

131
00:08:55,610 --> 00:08:56,720
Well, a friend of mine is over there.

132
00:08:56,720 --> 00:08:57,500
I should go say hi.

133
00:08:57,500 --> 00:08:58,780
Okay.

134
00:08:59,550 --> 00:09:00,620
You get back to the game.

135
00:09:00,620 --> 00:09:02,330
Must be Chinese. Sure thing.

136
00:09:15,130 --> 00:09:16,560
What a coincidence, Mr. Chen!

137
00:09:16,560 --> 00:09:17,440
Why are you

138
00:09:17,470 --> 00:09:19,040
eating bread alone?

139
00:09:24,410 --> 00:09:25,670
Where's your partner?

140
00:09:26,430 --> 00:09:27,560
Where's Luo Yingzi?

141
00:09:28,820 --> 00:09:29,820
Thanks to you,

142
00:09:29,840 --> 00:09:31,350
she has to stay in a hotel now.

143
00:09:31,350 --> 00:09:32,810
Don't you know about that?

144
00:09:35,160 --> 00:09:36,820
What does it have to do with me?

145
00:09:37,060 --> 00:09:38,190
She's not my client.

146
00:09:38,210 --> 00:09:39,740
Why are you telling me this?

147
00:09:42,470 --> 00:09:44,260
Doesn't it affect your mood at all?

148
00:09:44,260 --> 00:09:45,140
No.

149
00:09:45,420 --> 00:09:46,620
Does it affect yours?

150
00:09:50,020 --> 00:09:51,660
I really can't understand

151
00:09:52,160 --> 00:09:53,390
how you could be this happy.

152
00:09:53,390 --> 00:09:54,540
What's hard to understand?

153
00:09:54,540 --> 00:09:55,310
I'm confused.

154
00:09:55,310 --> 00:09:57,170
Is this your way of working a case?

155
00:09:57,510 --> 00:09:59,180
Your client suffers misfortune.

156
00:09:59,180 --> 00:09:59,720
But what can you do about it?

157
00:09:59,720 --> 00:10:00,850
Die with the client?

158
00:10:02,330 --> 00:10:04,260
Do you have to be so mean?

159
00:10:05,490 --> 00:10:06,750
I'm just being honest.

160
00:10:12,120 --> 00:10:14,180
How many years have you been a lawyer?

161
00:10:15,130 --> 00:10:16,130
I'm still a pupil.

162
00:10:16,330 --> 00:10:17,570
Now I understand.

163
00:10:19,610 --> 00:10:20,490
As a lawyer who's senior to you,

164
00:10:20,490 --> 00:10:22,130
I'll give you a piece of advice.

165
00:10:22,130 --> 00:10:22,770
Lawyers

166
00:10:22,840 --> 00:10:24,120
should draw a boundary

167
00:10:25,250 --> 00:10:27,110
between their own lives and work.

168
00:10:27,610 --> 00:10:28,610
Clients live their lives,

169
00:10:28,610 --> 00:10:29,360
and you live yours.

170
00:10:29,360 --> 00:10:30,200
You are paid by clients

171
00:10:30,200 --> 00:10:32,480
to represent them in court. It's your duty.

172
00:10:32,480 --> 00:10:33,490
The bottom line is,

173
00:10:33,490 --> 00:10:35,530
you work as a lawyer only to earn a living.

174
00:10:35,530 --> 00:10:37,730
You personal life should stay out of it.

175
00:10:40,590 --> 00:10:41,390
Do you hear me?

176
00:10:43,990 --> 00:10:45,590
Is it supposed to be a lesson?

177
00:10:46,760 --> 00:10:48,250
You're a cold-blooded animal.

178
00:10:48,250 --> 00:10:49,250
Whatever you say.

179
00:10:50,850 --> 00:10:51,920
Forget the bread.

180
00:10:51,940 --> 00:10:52,580
You poor thing.

181
00:10:52,580 --> 00:10:53,480
My friends are here.

182
00:10:53,480 --> 00:10:54,680
Why don't you join us?

183
00:10:54,720 --> 00:10:55,980
I don't need your pity.

184
00:10:56,000 --> 00:10:57,210
I don't enjoy being in a crowd.

185
00:10:57,210 --> 00:10:57,990
What a dull person!

186
00:10:57,990 --> 00:10:59,990
Then sit here by yourself and mourn.

187
00:11:18,330 --> 00:11:18,920
Come on.

188
00:11:20,180 --> 00:11:21,150
Fat or thin?

189
00:11:21,360 --> 00:11:22,310
Both.

190
00:11:22,720 --> 00:11:23,600
It depends on which dynasty.

191
00:11:23,600 --> 00:11:24,840
Both fat and thin?

192
00:11:24,860 --> 00:11:25,900
Excuse me.

193
00:11:27,760 --> 00:11:29,270
Mr. Chen, it's your umbrella.

194
00:11:29,270 --> 00:11:30,330
You should keep it.

195
00:11:33,000 --> 00:11:33,870
Give me your phone number.

196
00:11:33,870 --> 00:11:36,000
We have to stay in contact for the case.

197
00:11:36,640 --> 00:11:38,040
Is it really for the case?

198
00:11:40,200 --> 00:11:41,130
Just kidding.

199
00:11:41,260 --> 00:11:42,660
Fine. Give me your phone.

200
00:11:47,530 --> 00:11:48,050
Done.

201
00:11:53,090 --> 00:11:54,970
Borrow an umbrella and then give it back.

202
00:11:54,970 --> 00:11:56,300
That's a classic trick.

203
00:11:56,760 --> 00:11:57,400
Shuo,

204
00:11:57,640 --> 00:11:58,750
good for you.

205
00:11:58,790 --> 00:12:00,700
Not good at all. She's got a sulky face.

206
00:12:00,700 --> 00:12:02,160
It is not much to my liking.

207
00:12:02,660 --> 00:12:04,720
Now you think you're too good for her!

208
00:12:08,650 --> 00:12:09,320
Liu Ming,

209
00:12:10,330 --> 00:12:13,530
I hope you'll reply if you see this e-mail.

210
00:12:14,660 --> 00:12:16,970
The bank took our apartment yesterday.

211
00:12:17,490 --> 00:12:19,150
I was kicked out of my own home.

212
00:12:19,560 --> 00:12:21,880
I had to move out on a rainy night.

213
00:12:22,840 --> 00:12:25,640
You put a mortgage on the apartment behind my back.

214
00:12:26,600 --> 00:12:28,410
Do you know how much I hate you?

215
00:12:29,100 --> 00:12:31,530
People advised me to call the police,

216
00:12:31,770 --> 00:12:33,230
and charge you with fraud.

217
00:12:33,890 --> 00:12:36,220
Do you know how long you could be in prison?

218
00:12:36,760 --> 00:12:38,100
3 to 10 years,

219
00:12:38,600 --> 00:12:40,010
or even longer.

220
00:12:40,850 --> 00:12:41,500
Liu Ming,

221
00:12:42,600 --> 00:12:44,010
why did you do this to me?

222
00:12:45,010 --> 00:12:46,810
I want an explanation.

223
00:12:49,310 --> 00:12:50,840
Will it be something I like?

224
00:12:51,200 --> 00:12:52,330
Who knows?

225
00:12:52,830 --> 00:12:53,600
Come on.

226
00:12:53,620 --> 00:12:54,220
Look...

227
00:12:54,490 --> 00:12:56,610
Is it possible that I wouldn't like this?

228
00:12:56,610 --> 00:12:57,370
I've gotta go and make a call.

229
00:12:57,370 --> 00:12:58,250
Not quite possible.

230
00:12:58,250 --> 00:12:58,890
But...

231
00:12:59,000 --> 00:12:59,970
Why do you have to go again?

232
00:12:59,970 --> 00:13:00,520
I'll be right back.

233
00:13:00,520 --> 00:13:01,900
There's no way I wouldn't like this...

234
00:13:01,900 --> 00:13:03,300
Listen up...

235
00:13:03,360 --> 00:13:04,130
Is something going on?

236
00:13:04,130 --> 00:13:05,390
Something is going on.

237
00:13:05,480 --> 00:13:08,370
Come on. Cheers!

238
00:13:22,180 --> 00:13:23,210
Thanks to you,

239
00:13:23,210 --> 00:13:24,750
Luo Yingzi has to stay in a hotel now.

240
00:13:24,750 --> 00:13:25,880
Don't you know about that?

241
00:13:25,880 --> 00:13:27,610
You didn't leave her a chance.

242
00:13:28,730 --> 00:13:31,190
She can't get back to her apartment anymore.

243
00:13:35,410 --> 00:13:36,310
She's in a hotel...

244
00:13:36,310 --> 00:13:40,610
[Luo Yingzi]

245
00:13:37,730 --> 00:13:40,360
Should I call her?

246
00:13:52,720 --> 00:13:54,830
[Unscrupulous Chen]

247
00:13:56,490 --> 00:13:58,090
I shouldn't have called her.

248
00:14:00,960 --> 00:14:01,890
Yingzi,

249
00:14:02,750 --> 00:14:04,390
why are you still up?

250
00:14:05,130 --> 00:14:05,860
Don't worry.

251
00:14:06,730 --> 00:14:08,190
Just go back to your sleep.

252
00:14:43,090 --> 00:14:44,620
Are you not going to sue him?

253
00:14:47,490 --> 00:14:49,110
No. Not now.

254
00:14:51,600 --> 00:14:53,260
Do you still have hopes on him?

255
00:14:54,730 --> 00:14:55,970
At this point,

256
00:14:56,000 --> 00:14:57,600
who am I to hope for anything?

257
00:14:57,880 --> 00:14:59,940
If you don't accuse Liu Ming of fraud,

258
00:15:00,530 --> 00:15:03,250
you'll barely win the lawsuits you're in.

259
00:15:04,090 --> 00:15:05,360
I'm fine with anything.

260
00:15:05,360 --> 00:15:07,350
All cases mean resources to me.

261
00:15:07,760 --> 00:15:09,220
But Ms. Fang is different.

262
00:15:09,910 --> 00:15:12,230
She values her career and reputation.

263
00:15:14,160 --> 00:15:16,490
Do you know why she didn't charge you more?

264
00:15:16,600 --> 00:15:17,970
Because she thought

265
00:15:18,250 --> 00:15:20,150
you would lose anyway.

266
00:15:24,400 --> 00:15:26,770
I've been pondering it over and over again.

267
00:15:26,770 --> 00:15:28,370
But I still don't think I will

268
00:15:28,890 --> 00:15:31,020
go as far as to report him to the police.

269
00:15:32,730 --> 00:15:34,720
Despite what has happened,

270
00:15:34,910 --> 00:15:36,070
I still think

271
00:15:36,310 --> 00:15:38,320
Ming is the person I used to know.

272
00:15:39,610 --> 00:15:40,810
He's not a bad person,

273
00:15:41,230 --> 00:15:43,030
though he appears a little weak.

274
00:15:43,650 --> 00:15:45,780
He lets others make decisions for him.

275
00:15:45,890 --> 00:15:47,890
At first, he listened to his mother.

276
00:15:48,350 --> 00:15:50,610
Then he married me.

277
00:15:51,290 --> 00:15:53,750
I thought he'd let me decide for him forever.

278
00:15:54,770 --> 00:15:57,100
Unexpectedly, he turned to someone else.

279
00:15:57,360 --> 00:15:58,970
I just don't understand.

280
00:15:59,650 --> 00:16:01,890
It's true that he cheated on me with Wen Li.

281
00:16:01,890 --> 00:16:04,250
But does that mean he has to be cruel to me

282
00:16:04,820 --> 00:16:05,880
and make me suffer?

283
00:16:07,130 --> 00:16:09,120
Before I could find an answer,

284
00:16:09,840 --> 00:16:11,860
I won't choose the ultimate resort.

285
00:16:16,210 --> 00:16:16,850
Fine.

286
00:16:17,250 --> 00:16:19,310
Then prepare yourself for the worst.

287
00:16:36,610 --> 00:16:38,740
Isn't it where Qin Ailian used to work?

288
00:16:40,550 --> 00:16:41,810
Why do you think of her?

289
00:17:05,680 --> 00:17:08,890
About a month before Qin Ailian's death.

290
00:17:09,490 --> 00:17:10,760
Do you know why?

291
00:17:11,359 --> 00:17:13,170
I don't.

292
00:17:13,369 --> 00:17:15,520
I was on vacation when he left.

293
00:17:16,839 --> 00:17:17,970
But I heard

294
00:17:17,970 --> 00:17:19,690
he was fired by the boss

295
00:17:19,770 --> 00:17:20,970
for a mistake at work.

296
00:17:23,079 --> 00:17:24,650
Sir, what can I get you?

297
00:17:25,680 --> 00:17:26,540
Some lamp soup.

298
00:17:27,119 --> 00:17:28,160
What are you doing here?

299
00:17:28,160 --> 00:17:29,200
I'm here to eat.

300
00:17:30,050 --> 00:17:31,450
Go on with the interview.

301
00:17:33,700 --> 00:17:34,790
Among all the restaurants in Jingbei,

302
00:17:34,790 --> 00:17:36,170
why did you come here in particular?

303
00:17:36,170 --> 00:17:37,700
The food here is delicious.

304
00:17:37,700 --> 00:17:40,100
Are you still working on Qin Ailian's case?

305
00:17:41,320 --> 00:17:42,800
You see right through me.

306
00:17:43,250 --> 00:17:44,720
Captain Wang, don't be so uptight.

307
00:17:44,720 --> 00:17:46,580
Have the police found something?

308
00:17:47,510 --> 00:17:48,440
Tell me about it.

309
00:17:48,580 --> 00:17:49,820
Stay out of this.

310
00:17:50,840 --> 00:17:52,690
When we turn an arrested suspect over to the prosecutor's office,

311
00:17:52,690 --> 00:17:55,130
you'll get your chance to earn contingency.

312
00:17:55,130 --> 00:17:55,570
You've gotta go now.

313
00:17:55,570 --> 00:17:56,610
Fine. You do your thing.

314
00:17:56,610 --> 00:17:57,530
I get it. I'll go.

315
00:17:57,530 --> 00:17:58,760
Go. Go in there.

316
00:18:08,050 --> 00:18:08,780
Hey, Mr. Xue.

317
00:18:09,120 --> 00:18:10,250
Can you come out now?

318
00:18:11,050 --> 00:18:13,930
You know the restaurant that Qin Ailin used to work in, don't you?

319
00:18:13,930 --> 00:18:15,040
I was just passing by when I saw

320
00:18:15,040 --> 00:18:17,450
Wang Rui interviewing an waitress.

321
00:18:17,750 --> 00:18:19,400
You should come and get some information.

322
00:18:19,400 --> 00:18:21,610
Let's see if the waitress has revealed

323
00:18:21,610 --> 00:18:22,920
something we don't know.

324
00:18:22,920 --> 00:18:23,650
Is that okay?

325
00:18:28,760 --> 00:18:29,450
Over these days,

326
00:18:29,450 --> 00:18:31,330
we have collected some evidence.

327
00:18:31,400 --> 00:18:33,810
Of course, the credit goes to Qiu Hua.

328
00:18:34,470 --> 00:18:37,070
We have Grand Property's registration papers

329
00:18:37,610 --> 00:18:41,410
and the bank statements of your and Liu Ming's accounts,

330
00:18:41,520 --> 00:18:43,470
plus the proof of your previous income.

331
00:18:43,470 --> 00:18:44,980
We plan to show in court

332
00:18:45,010 --> 00:18:45,800
that the company

333
00:18:45,800 --> 00:18:48,120
never made a transfer to your account.

334
00:18:48,290 --> 00:18:50,880
Your income was used for family expenditure.

335
00:18:51,400 --> 00:18:53,130
But I don't think

336
00:18:54,520 --> 00:18:56,150
what we have here is persuasive enough

337
00:18:56,150 --> 00:18:58,750
to separate you from the corporate debts.

338
00:18:59,160 --> 00:19:01,440
Half a year before Liu Ming ran away,

339
00:19:01,440 --> 00:19:03,360
he started to borrow private loans.

340
00:19:03,360 --> 00:19:05,570
So the court is very likely to rule

341
00:19:05,640 --> 00:19:08,330
that the debts were borrowed to pay for

342
00:19:08,350 --> 00:19:10,680
operation costs and family expenditure.

343
00:19:11,360 --> 00:19:12,300
Therefore, Yingzi,

344
00:19:12,300 --> 00:19:13,570
you need to prepare yourself

345
00:19:13,570 --> 00:19:15,320
to repay those private loans.

346
00:19:15,900 --> 00:19:17,230
I understand, Ms. Fang.

347
00:19:17,800 --> 00:19:19,730
In fact, since the very beginning,

348
00:19:20,130 --> 00:19:22,460
I've always known that I'll lose the case.

349
00:19:23,250 --> 00:19:24,610
I just want a closure

350
00:19:24,650 --> 00:19:26,370
with these people in court.

351
00:19:28,850 --> 00:19:31,440
As long as I could make it to court,

352
00:19:31,960 --> 00:19:33,690
I'll consider myself a winner.

353
00:19:34,370 --> 00:19:36,500
I'm just sorry that I got you involved.

354
00:19:37,360 --> 00:19:38,810
In recent years,

355
00:19:38,810 --> 00:19:40,540
you have rarely lost any cases.

356
00:19:40,560 --> 00:19:42,760
My case may be a disgrace on your record.

357
00:19:43,830 --> 00:19:45,090
That's not important.

358
00:19:45,340 --> 00:19:47,390
I've promised to represent you,

359
00:19:47,930 --> 00:19:49,900
and prepared myself for failure.

360
00:19:51,270 --> 00:19:53,310
It is actually a good thing

361
00:19:53,600 --> 00:19:55,320
that the apartment is taken by the bank.

362
00:19:55,320 --> 00:19:56,180
Think about it.

363
00:19:56,210 --> 00:19:58,090
If those private loan companies

364
00:19:58,090 --> 00:20:00,030
know you still own a real estate asset,

365
00:20:00,030 --> 00:20:01,430
it'll be a huge disaster.

366
00:20:01,560 --> 00:20:02,790
They won't easily cut you loose.

367
00:20:02,790 --> 00:20:03,520
That's true.

368
00:20:04,230 --> 00:20:06,790
About Liu Ming's bank statements,

369
00:20:06,810 --> 00:20:08,270
I found something unsual.

370
00:20:09,900 --> 00:20:11,160
He seldom spent money.

371
00:20:11,640 --> 00:20:12,880
The money he borrowed

372
00:20:13,050 --> 00:20:15,380
was used to run the company and was all lost

373
00:20:15,400 --> 00:20:17,210
due to bad management.

374
00:20:17,760 --> 00:20:19,890
If it weren't for this last 10 million,

375
00:20:20,290 --> 00:20:21,650
even I would rather believe

376
00:20:21,650 --> 00:20:23,650
that he's just a lousy businessman,

377
00:20:23,970 --> 00:20:25,900
and that he didn't mean to hurt you.

378
00:20:26,650 --> 00:20:28,850
That's what I've been thinking as well.

379
00:20:29,520 --> 00:20:32,920
It's why I hesitate and haven't charged him with fraud.

380
00:20:34,470 --> 00:20:36,030
Just clear your mind.

381
00:20:36,530 --> 00:20:38,130
Go back and have a good sleep.

382
00:20:38,440 --> 00:20:40,790
Get ready for tomorrow's trial.

383
00:20:52,500 --> 00:20:54,030
I'm exhausted.

384
00:20:54,530 --> 00:20:56,590
Come on. It's not even that much work.

385
00:20:57,050 --> 00:20:58,530
Have you found anything?

386
00:20:59,790 --> 00:21:00,690
You've got a lead.

387
00:21:00,690 --> 00:21:02,510
Why don't you investigate it by yourself?

388
00:21:02,510 --> 00:21:03,730
You just enjoy picking on me.

389
00:21:03,730 --> 00:21:04,130
Don't say that.

390
00:21:04,130 --> 00:21:05,320
I didn't want to run into Wang Rui again.

391
00:21:05,320 --> 00:21:07,450
That would be utterly inappropriate.

392
00:21:07,740 --> 00:21:09,980
I've been to the Elegant Club

393
00:21:10,000 --> 00:21:11,770
and the restaurant where Qin Ailian worked.

394
00:21:11,770 --> 00:21:12,970
I did find something.

395
00:21:13,370 --> 00:21:14,300
Give me a second.

396
00:21:14,710 --> 00:21:15,310
Send me.

397
00:21:18,370 --> 00:21:19,630
You should have it now.

398
00:21:20,360 --> 00:21:21,420
This man is Wu Hang.

399
00:21:21,530 --> 00:21:23,610
He used to be a journalism student at Jingbei University.

400
00:21:23,610 --> 00:21:26,140
He graduated top of the class the year before.

401
00:21:26,370 --> 00:21:27,770
Was he Qin Ailian's boyfriend?

402
00:21:27,770 --> 00:21:28,500
I don't know.

403
00:21:29,130 --> 00:21:31,370
The first time he went to the Elegant Club,

404
00:21:31,370 --> 00:21:32,140
he was still a university student.

405
00:21:32,140 --> 00:21:33,860
I guess he was a patron there.

406
00:21:34,210 --> 00:21:35,490
I'm not sure

407
00:21:35,570 --> 00:21:37,060
if they knew each other at that time.

408
00:21:37,060 --> 00:21:38,210
Guess what?

409
00:21:38,840 --> 00:21:40,040
After graduation,

410
00:21:40,060 --> 00:21:41,800
Wu Hang didn't seek a proper job.

411
00:21:41,800 --> 00:21:43,880
He began working in the Elegant Club.

412
00:21:44,720 --> 00:21:45,680
What kind of job could a young man like him

413
00:21:45,680 --> 00:21:47,430
do in the Elegant Club?

414
00:21:47,610 --> 00:21:49,810
The answer is pretty obvious, isn't it?

415
00:21:52,690 --> 00:21:54,690
That means they did know each other.

416
00:21:54,690 --> 00:21:55,280
Right?

417
00:21:55,790 --> 00:21:56,830
There's more.

418
00:21:57,540 --> 00:21:59,990
3 months before Qin Ailian died,

419
00:22:00,490 --> 00:22:02,850
Wu Hang took a part-time job

420
00:22:02,890 --> 00:22:04,210
at the restaurant she worked in.

421
00:22:04,210 --> 00:22:06,460
But in less than 2 months, he was fired.

422
00:22:06,970 --> 00:22:07,900
For what reason?

423
00:22:08,210 --> 00:22:09,210
The employer said

424
00:22:09,720 --> 00:22:11,320
a drunk customer

425
00:22:11,350 --> 00:22:13,010
harassed Qin Ailian.

426
00:22:13,030 --> 00:22:14,360
Wu Hang beat him up.

427
00:22:15,130 --> 00:22:16,350
Being afraid of bearing liabilities,

428
00:22:16,350 --> 00:22:17,950
the employer sacked Wu Hang.

429
00:22:18,270 --> 00:22:19,900
I've just looked at his photo.

430
00:22:19,900 --> 00:22:21,890
He doesn't appear to be a violent person.

431
00:22:21,890 --> 00:22:23,820
You can't judge a book by its cover.

432
00:22:24,380 --> 00:22:26,530
What's wrong with today's young people?

433
00:22:26,530 --> 00:22:28,130
Wu Hang went to a good university.

434
00:22:28,130 --> 00:22:29,930
He could have taken a better job.

435
00:22:30,160 --> 00:22:32,160
He even has a postgraduate diploma.

436
00:22:35,160 --> 00:22:37,080
Keep an eye on your son.

437
00:22:37,410 --> 00:22:39,930
He's always been an overachiever at school,

438
00:22:39,930 --> 00:22:40,970
but he possibly has done many awful things

439
00:22:40,970 --> 00:22:42,610
behind your back.

440
00:22:44,290 --> 00:22:46,120
My naughty child

441
00:22:46,690 --> 00:22:48,360
has developed a worse and worse temper

442
00:22:48,360 --> 00:22:49,970
since he went to the middle school.

443
00:22:49,970 --> 00:22:51,580
He talks back to his mom.

444
00:22:51,600 --> 00:22:53,280
They argue and argue.

445
00:22:53,690 --> 00:22:55,250
It's okay. Don't worry.

446
00:22:55,650 --> 00:22:58,050
As long as he doesn't cross the boundary,

447
00:22:58,070 --> 00:23:00,780
you should forgive him for being a bit rebellious.

448
00:23:00,780 --> 00:23:01,440
You shouldn't be

449
00:23:01,440 --> 00:23:03,040
as strict with him as before.

450
00:23:03,260 --> 00:23:04,240
Or he'll be under enormous pressure,

451
00:23:04,240 --> 00:23:06,580
have a huge meltdown one day,

452
00:23:06,600 --> 00:23:07,610
and go for self destruction.

453
00:23:07,610 --> 00:23:09,810
If so, you and your wife will be sorry...

454
00:23:13,440 --> 00:23:14,970
Self destruction...

455
00:23:16,120 --> 00:23:16,800
Mr. Xue,

456
00:23:17,500 --> 00:23:18,410
look into Wu Hang's relationship

457
00:23:18,410 --> 00:23:19,680
with his parents.

458
00:23:24,930 --> 00:23:25,990
I'm talking to you!

459
00:23:26,480 --> 00:23:29,000
Well, though you always talk about money,

460
00:23:30,130 --> 00:23:31,850
I can still detect

461
00:23:32,280 --> 00:23:34,610
that you're somewhat a righteous person.

462
00:23:34,750 --> 00:23:36,040
We are different.

463
00:23:36,290 --> 00:23:37,680
I have a son to raise.

464
00:23:38,130 --> 00:23:39,900
We've agreed to split the contingency in half.

465
00:23:39,900 --> 00:23:41,270
I'm gonna get every penny I deserve.

466
00:23:41,270 --> 00:23:41,820
Hey.

467
00:23:42,570 --> 00:23:44,210
I only took 20% for the first trial.

468
00:23:44,210 --> 00:23:46,090
And I did all the work.

469
00:23:46,290 --> 00:23:47,640
That's different.

470
00:23:48,370 --> 00:23:50,690
Back then we were only doing a lawyer's job.

471
00:23:50,690 --> 00:23:53,090
But now I'm doing a private investigator's job too.

472
00:23:53,090 --> 00:23:55,130
It's very dangerous.

473
00:23:56,120 --> 00:23:56,980
How about this?

474
00:23:57,450 --> 00:23:59,200
I'll do all the leg work,

475
00:23:59,200 --> 00:24:01,120
while you ask the clients

476
00:24:01,120 --> 00:24:03,370
to pay us more.

477
00:24:03,610 --> 00:24:04,220
Is it okay?

478
00:24:04,880 --> 00:24:05,610
I’ll start working now.

479
00:24:05,610 --> 00:24:07,600
We'll split the money in half. Not a penny less.

480
00:24:07,600 --> 00:24:09,050
I'll get down to work now.

481
00:24:10,360 --> 00:24:11,290
Not a penny less.

482
00:24:18,120 --> 00:24:19,330
Self destruction.

483
00:24:28,610 --> 00:24:29,210
Come in.

484
00:24:30,110 --> 00:24:32,090
This is our new home.

485
00:24:33,000 --> 00:24:34,120
That's your room.

486
00:24:34,300 --> 00:24:35,470
Go and check it out.

487
00:24:40,890 --> 00:24:41,780
Not bad, right?

488
00:24:41,820 --> 00:24:43,030
It's lovely.

489
00:24:43,220 --> 00:24:45,850
It's way worse than before.

490
00:24:45,880 --> 00:24:47,650
Just accept the changes.

491
00:24:48,020 --> 00:24:49,570
We should be glad that we have a home.

492
00:24:49,570 --> 00:24:50,900
It's good enough for us.

493
00:24:51,960 --> 00:24:53,560
The kitchen is big, isn't it?

494
00:24:54,690 --> 00:24:56,400
Why is there a musty smell?

495
00:24:56,420 --> 00:24:57,690
I haven't cleaned it yet.

496
00:24:57,690 --> 00:24:59,490
It'll be fine when it's cleaned.

497
00:25:00,360 --> 00:25:00,890
Yingzi,

498
00:25:01,400 --> 00:25:03,720
why would there be evil people?

499
00:25:04,760 --> 00:25:06,490
Humans have lived for so many years.

500
00:25:06,490 --> 00:25:07,330
Yet no one

501
00:25:07,360 --> 00:25:09,890
has learned all the truth about human nature.

502
00:25:10,080 --> 00:25:11,880
Lanlan, don't think about that.

503
00:25:11,950 --> 00:25:13,410
Let's clean this place

504
00:25:13,440 --> 00:25:15,110
and live a good life.

505
00:25:15,920 --> 00:25:18,330
However, to be honest,

506
00:25:18,880 --> 00:25:21,130
there probably will be a difficult time

507
00:25:21,200 --> 00:25:23,650
ahead of us.

508
00:25:24,650 --> 00:25:26,400
If you don't like this place...

509
00:25:26,930 --> 00:25:29,050
We'll stick together in all the good and bad times.

510
00:25:29,050 --> 00:25:30,970
Yingzi, I want to study law with you

511
00:25:30,970 --> 00:25:32,100
and become a lawyer.

512
00:25:32,680 --> 00:25:34,200
Let's go for it!

513
00:25:34,600 --> 00:25:35,210
Clean up the place now.

514
00:25:35,210 --> 00:25:38,880
Yingzi, this mess is giving me a headache!

515
00:25:38,880 --> 00:25:39,920
Put your stuff into your room.

516
00:25:39,920 --> 00:25:42,530
Doing everything all over again. My god!

517
00:25:42,530 --> 00:25:43,810
I'll place mine in my room.

518
00:25:43,810 --> 00:25:45,540
Let's clean the kitchen later.

519
00:25:59,240 --> 00:26:02,890
♫I'm following♫

520
00:26:03,700 --> 00:26:06,520
♫Where the wind blows♫

521
00:26:09,720 --> 00:26:13,920
♫Chasing the sun and soil♫

522
00:26:15,740 --> 00:26:19,850
♫Growing freely♫

523
00:26:23,190 --> 00:26:26,890
♫The wind says♫

524
00:26:27,570 --> 00:26:31,600
♫Keep chasing♫

525
00:26:33,600 --> 00:26:38,710
♫Be a true believer♫

526
00:26:34,240 --> 00:26:34,970
I can make it!

527
00:26:39,620 --> 00:26:43,550
♫And don't be distracted♫

528
00:26:50,380 --> 00:26:52,560
[Jingbei Court]

529
00:26:50,880 --> 00:26:51,880
Court adjourned.

530
00:26:55,320 --> 00:26:55,980
Defendant,

531
00:26:57,090 --> 00:26:58,410
if possible,

532
00:26:58,610 --> 00:27:00,330
try to pay off some debts first.

533
00:27:00,330 --> 00:27:01,930
If the repayment is overdue,

534
00:27:02,080 --> 00:27:04,360
the plaintiff is entitled to confiscate your property.

535
00:27:04,360 --> 00:27:05,000
Thank you.

536
00:27:08,260 --> 00:27:09,390
Defense counsel...

537
00:27:14,880 --> 00:27:15,680
Ms. Luo.

538
00:27:16,090 --> 00:27:17,220
I'm sorry, Ms. Fang.

539
00:27:17,800 --> 00:27:19,570
Don't say that.

540
00:27:20,890 --> 00:27:23,400
Can you pay the debts or not?

541
00:27:23,650 --> 00:27:25,310
If you can't, the lawyer's fees...

542
00:27:25,310 --> 00:27:26,460
I'll handle my own business.

543
00:27:26,460 --> 00:27:27,060
Ms. Fang,

544
00:27:27,450 --> 00:27:28,450
you and Qiu Hua

545
00:27:28,560 --> 00:27:30,390
have finished your work here.

546
00:27:30,880 --> 00:27:32,620
I'll take care of the rest.

547
00:27:35,850 --> 00:27:38,550
These gang-backed companies can be brutal.

548
00:27:39,610 --> 00:27:41,290
If you don't pay them back,

549
00:27:41,360 --> 00:27:43,760
they'll surely make a scene in the law firm.

550
00:27:43,840 --> 00:27:46,340
By then, I can't protect you even if I want to.

551
00:27:47,770 --> 00:27:49,520
I'll settle with them.

552
00:27:50,690 --> 00:27:52,970
Money is the solution to many problems.

553
00:28:22,330 --> 00:28:25,370
Money is the solution to many problems.

554
00:28:34,280 --> 00:28:34,900
Ms. Fang,

555
00:28:36,130 --> 00:28:38,080
Liang, the newly qualified attorney

556
00:28:38,080 --> 00:28:39,760
in the civil case department, is a disgrace.

557
00:28:39,760 --> 00:28:41,330
He went to a pedicure salon and had a fight

558
00:28:41,330 --> 00:28:43,260
with the business owner about money.

559
00:28:43,260 --> 00:28:44,320
They got physical,

560
00:28:44,470 --> 00:28:46,400
and ended up in the police station.

561
00:28:46,780 --> 00:28:47,720
Just bail him out.

562
00:28:47,720 --> 00:28:48,520
Then sack him.

563
00:28:57,880 --> 00:28:58,800
Sack him?

564
00:29:00,760 --> 00:29:02,020
His life's quite hard.

565
00:29:02,600 --> 00:29:03,880
His family has met multiple difficulties.

566
00:29:03,880 --> 00:29:05,400
He's the only person his family counts on.

567
00:29:05,400 --> 00:29:06,210
Fire him.

568
00:29:08,600 --> 00:29:10,330
Our law firm is not a sanctuary.

